article.headline: Quinnipiac 55, Cornell 45
article.story: ITHACA, N.Y. (AP) -- Adam Gonzalez scored 10 of his 18 points in the second half to lead Quinnipiac to a 55-45 victory over Cornell Friday night. Gonzalez made 11-of-12 free throws for the Bobcats (3-2), who held the Big Red to 15 points in the second half. Chris Wehye added 12 points, while Victor Akinyanju had nine rebounds and blocked four shots. Cornell (2-5) built a 22-15 lead in the first half before Quinnipiac responded with seven straight points. The Big Red led 30-26 at halftime. In the second half, the score was tied three times before the Bobcats went on an 11-2 run to make it 48-39 with less than four minutes remaining. Adam Gore led Cornell with nine points as the Big Red shot 34 percent. Quinnipiac, which shot 38 percent, came into the game averaging 80 points.
